  "text": "We start by reviewing the problem of answering queries using views for conjunctive queries (i.e., select-project-join queries). A conjunctive query CQ is a query of the form: Chandra and Merlin [CITATION_1] show that a conjunctive query Q 1 is contained in another conjunctive query Q 2 if and only if there is a containment mapping from Q 2 to Q 1 . The containment mapping maps the head and all the subgoals in Q 2 to Q 1 . It maps each variable to either a variable or a constant, and maps each constant to the same constant. Concerning unions of CQs, the following containment test is from [CITATION_2] ; a union of CQs",
